data.text:
From a compound of Bach (“creek, stream”) with an unclear first element, possibly a given name.

IPA(key): /ˈɔfn̩ˌbax/

Audio:

Hyphenation: Of‧fen‧bach

Offenbach n (proper noun, genitive Offenbachs or (optionally with an article) Offenbach)

An independent city in Hesse. Official name: Offenbach am Main

A rural district of Hesse. Seat: Dietzenbach

A municipality of Südliche Weinstraße district, Rhineland-Palatinate. Official name: Offenbach an der Queich

Offenbach m or f (proper noun, surname, masculine genitive Offenbachs or (with an article) Offenbach, feminine genitive Offenbach, plural Offenbachs)
